## 2. What data do we collect and why?

### 2.1 Contact form

When you fill in the contact form on our website, we process:

- Name
- Company name (optional)
- Phone number (optional)
- Email address
- The content of your message

**Purpose:** answering your enquiry or following up on your support request.  
**Legal basis:** performance of a contract or pre-contractual steps (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR), or our legitimate interest in responding to enquiries (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).

### 2.2 Website analytics (Google Analytics via Google Tag Manager)

We use Google Analytics (via Google Tag Manager) to collect anonymous statistics about the use of our website, such as page views, session duration and visitor origin. Full IP addresses are not stored.

**Purpose:** understanding how the website is used in order to improve it.  
**Legal basis:** consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR). You can withdraw consent at any time via the cookie settings in the footer.

### 2.3 Behavioural analytics (Microsoft Clarity)

With your consent, we use Microsoft Clarity for heatmaps and session recordings. Clarity collects anonymised interaction data (mouse movements, clicks, scroll behaviour). Personally identifiable information is automatically masked.

**Purpose:** improving the user experience on the website.  
**Legal basis:** consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR). You can withdraw consent via the cookie settings in the footer.

### 2.4 Client and assignment data

In the context of an assignment or support contract, we process contact details and technical information needed to perform the service.

**Purpose:** performance of the contract and compliance with legal obligations.  
**Legal basis:** contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR) and legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR).

